1
00:01:12,946 --> 00:01:15,031
Pull yourself together Teddy!

2
00:01:15,115 --> 00:01:16,616
Pull yourself together!

3
00:01:21,872 --> 00:01:23,457
It's just water.

4
00:01:25,417 --> 00:01:27,335
It's a lot of water.

5
00:01:33,758 --> 00:01:34,551
Come on.

6
00:01:58,450 --> 00:02:03,205
- You okay boss?
- Yeah, I'm fine. I just... I just can't

7
00:02:03,914 --> 00:02:06,792
I just can't stomach the water.

8
00:02:08,794 --> 00:02:12,631
- So you're my new partner?
- That's right.

9
00:02:13,173 --> 00:02:16,009
Not the best way to meet with my head
halfway down the toilet.

10
00:02:16,009 --> 00:02:19,805
Doesn't exactly square with Teddy Daniels:
The man. The legend. I'll give you that.

11
00:02:19,805 --> 00:02:20,889
The Legend?

12
00:02:21,848 --> 00:02:24,101
What the hell are you boys smoking
out there in Portland anyway?

13
00:02:24,142 --> 00:02:24,810
Seattle.

14
00:02:25,894 --> 00:02:29,022
I came from the office in Seattle.

15
00:02:30,232 --> 00:02:32,275
How long have you been with Marshals?

16
00:02:32,275 --> 00:02:33,318
Four years.

17
00:02:35,737 --> 00:02:38,365
- So you know how small it is?
- Sure

18
00:02:40,534 --> 00:02:43,870
What about you? You got a girl? Married?

19
00:02:44,496 --> 00:02:45,122
I was.

20
00:02:57,509 --> 00:02:58,385
She died.

21
00:02:59,386 --> 00:03:03,473
- Jesus... I didn't...
- Don't worry about it.

22
00:03:04,224 --> 00:03:07,436
There was a fire at the apartment
building while I was at work

23
00:03:07,436 --> 00:03:09,020
Four People died.

24
00:03:09,312 --> 00:03:12,649
It was the smoke that got her
not the fire. So...

25
00:03:12,649 --> 00:03:15,068
- So that's important.
- I'm sorry Boss.

26
00:03:15,068 --> 00:03:17,696
Where are my goddamn cigarettes?

27
00:03:19,322 --> 00:03:20,574
Well here. Have one of mine.

28
00:03:20,574 --> 00:03:24,035
I could of sworn they were in my jacket
when I got on.

29
00:03:24,035 --> 00:03:27,205
Government employees will rob you blind.

30
00:03:29,124 --> 00:03:29,708
Thanks.

31
00:03:31,501 --> 00:03:33,962
They give you a briefing
about the institution before you left?

32
00:03:33,962 --> 00:03:37,466
All I know is it's a mental hospital.

33
00:03:37,966 --> 00:03:40,385
For the criminally insane.

34
00:03:40,927 --> 00:03:43,096
Well, if it was just folks running around,
hearing voices,

35
00:03:43,096 --> 00:03:48,185
and chasing after butterflies,
they wouldn't need us.

36
00:03:55,901 --> 00:03:59,029
- That's where we're headed?
- Yup.

37
00:03:59,071 --> 00:04:01,573
The other side of the island is rock bluffs

38
00:04:01,615 --> 00:04:03,617
all the way down to the edge
of the water.

39
00:04:04,201 --> 00:04:07,954
The dock, it's the
only way on...or off.

40
00:04:08,372 --> 00:04:11,708
We will be casting off as soon as
you two are ashore.

41
00:04:11,708 --> 00:04:14,294
I'd appreciate if you'd hurry up about it.

42
00:04:14,294 --> 00:04:16,588
- Why?
- Storm's coming.

43
00:04:43,532 --> 00:04:47,285
I've never seen a marshal's
badge before.

44
00:04:48,328 --> 00:04:49,871
I'm Deputy Warden
McPherson, gentlemen.

45
00:04:49,871 --> 00:04:55,794
Welcome to Shutter Island.
I'll be the one taking you up to Ashecliffe.

46
00:05:06,555 --> 00:05:09,474
Your boys seem a little on edge
Mr. McPherson.

47
00:05:09,474 --> 00:05:12,310
Right now, Marshal. We all are.

48
00:05:29,286 --> 00:05:34,374
"Remember us for we too have
lived, loved and laughed"

49
00:05:55,812 --> 00:05:57,773
Electrified perimeter.

50
00:05:59,775 --> 00:06:01,026
How could you tell?

51
00:06:02,277 --> 00:06:05,572
I've seen something like it before.

52
00:06:33,141 --> 00:06:36,812
All right. You gentlemen will be accorded
all the help we can give.

53
00:06:36,812 --> 00:06:41,566
But during the stay you will
obey protocol. Is that understood?

54
00:06:41,566 --> 00:06:42,567
Absolutely.

55
00:06:43,485 --> 00:06:46,905
The red brick bulding on my right
is ward A, the male ward.

56
00:06:46,905 --> 00:06:49,908
Ward B, the female ward, is the one
on the left.

57
00:06:49,908 --> 00:06:53,412
Ward C is that building on the bluffs.
An old civil war fort.

58
00:06:55,122 --> 00:06:57,541
The most dangerous patients
are housed there.

59
00:06:57,541 --> 00:07:01,837
Admittance to ward C is forbidden without
the written consent and

60
00:07:01,837 --> 00:07:04,715
physical presence of both myself and Dr. Cawly.

61
00:07:04,715 --> 00:07:06,508
Is that understood?

62
00:07:07,634 --> 00:07:10,721
You act like insanity is catching.

63
00:07:13,015 --> 00:07:17,728
You are hereby required to surrending
your firearms.

64
00:07:17,811 --> 00:07:21,273
Mr. McPherson, we are duly appointed
federal marshals.

65
00:07:21,273 --> 00:07:23,775
We are required to carry our
firearms with us at all times.

66
00:07:23,775 --> 00:07:26,820
Executive order 319 of the Federal Code of
Penitentiaries states that:

67
00:07:26,820 --> 00:07:28,989
when inside the penitentiary

68
00:07:28,989 --> 00:07:34,161
the offices of that institution
have final authority.

69
00:07:35,245 --> 00:07:42,502
Gentlemen, you will not get through
this gate with your firearms.

70
00:07:58,477 --> 00:08:02,022
Okay. Now that the official stuff is done,
come on boys.

71
00:08:02,022 --> 00:08:05,651
What do you say we go find Dr. Cawley?

72
00:08:16,119 --> 00:08:18,914
So when did she escape? This prisoner?

73
00:08:18,914 --> 00:08:22,042
I'm afraid that Dr. Cawley will have to
fill you in on the situation.

74
00:08:22,042 --> 00:08:22,876
Protocol.

75
00:08:23,210 --> 00:08:25,462
Correctional officers at a mental institution.

76
00:08:25,462 --> 00:08:27,881
That's a weird sight,
if you don't mind me saying

77
00:08:27,881 --> 00:08:30,092
It's the only facility of it's kind in the U.S.
Even in the world.

78
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:33,845
We take only the
most dangerous, damaged patients.

79
00:08:33,845 --> 00:08:37,808
Ones no other hospital can manage.
And it's all due to Dr. Cawley.

80
00:08:37,808 --> 00:08:44,147
He's created something really unique here.
It's a hospital for people our society normally...

81
00:09:11,508 --> 00:09:13,010
ID's, gentlemen.

82
00:09:16,930 --> 00:09:18,557
Show your badges, gentlemen.

83
00:09:18,807 --> 00:09:21,101
Dr. Cawley's been consulted
numerous times

84
00:09:21,101 --> 00:09:25,314
- By Scotland Yard, MI5, the OSS...
- Why?

85
00:09:25,355 --> 00:09:27,024
What do you mean?

86
00:09:29,318 --> 00:09:32,988
What do intelligence agencies want
to consult a psychatrist about?

87
00:09:32,988 --> 00:09:35,908
I guess you'll have to ask him.

88
00:09:44,791 --> 00:09:47,377
- Marshal Daniels.
- Doctor.

89
00:09:47,377 --> 00:09:48,670
Marshal Aule.

90
00:09:49,463 --> 00:09:53,717
- Thank you deputy warden, that will be all.
- Yes, sir.

91
00:09:53,717 --> 00:09:55,511
Pleasure, gentlemen.

92
00:09:56,553 --> 00:09:58,347
He had a lot to say about you.

93
00:09:58,347 --> 00:10:01,475
McPherson is a good man.
He believes in the work we do here.

94
00:10:01,475 --> 00:10:03,936
And what would that be exactly?

95
00:10:03,936 --> 00:10:07,523
A moral fusion between law and
order and clinical care.

96
00:10:07,523 --> 00:10:11,818
Pardon me Doc...
a what between what and what?

97
00:10:17,407 --> 00:10:20,619
Those paintings are quite accurate.

98
00:10:20,619 --> 00:10:23,497
It used to be that the kind of patients we
deal with here

99
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:26,208
were shackled and left in their own filth.

100
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:29,545
They were beaten. As if whipping
them bloody would drive the psychosis out.

101
00:10:29,753 --> 00:10:36,343
We drove screws into their brains. We submerged
them in icy water until they lost consciousness.

102
00:10:36,343 --> 00:10:37,678
Or even drown.

103
00:10:38,303 --> 00:10:40,389
- And now?
- We treat them.

104
00:10:40,389 --> 00:10:42,641
Try to heal, try to cure.

105
00:10:42,891 --> 00:10:47,563
And if this fails, at least we provide them
with a measure of comfort in their lives. Calm.

106
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:48,689
These are...

107
00:10:49,565 --> 00:10:51,942
all violent offenders, right?

108
00:10:51,942 --> 00:10:53,819
They've hurt people.

109
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:58,115
- Murdered them in some cases.
- In almost all cases. Yes.

110
00:10:58,115 --> 00:11:03,871
Then personally Doctor, I'd have to
say... screw their sense of calm.

111
00:11:03,871 --> 00:11:07,791
It's my job to treat my patients not
their victims. I'm not here to judge.

112
00:11:07,791 --> 00:11:11,378
- So this female prisoner...
- Patient.

113
00:11:11,378 --> 00:11:15,007
Excuse me, patient.
One Rachel Solando,

114
00:11:16,049 --> 00:11:18,760
- Escaped sometime in the last 24 hours.

115
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:20,846
Last night, between 10 and midnight.

116
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:24,183
- Is she considered dangerous?
- You could say that.

117
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:26,685
She killed all three of her children.

118
00:11:26,685 --> 00:11:29,813
She drowned them in the lake behind her house.

119
00:11:29,813 --> 00:11:33,233
She took them out one by one and held their
heads under until they died.

120
00:11:33,233 --> 00:11:36,820
Then she brought them back inside and
arranged them around the kitchen table.

121
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:41,033
She ate a meal there
before a neighbor dropped by.

122
00:11:41,158 --> 00:11:42,743
And what about the husband?

123
00:11:42,743 --> 00:11:47,331
He died. On the beaches of Normandy.
She is a war widow.

124
00:11:47,331 --> 00:11:54,880
She starved herself when first she came here.
She insisted the children weren't dead.

125
00:12:02,304 --> 00:12:06,892
- Sorry doctor. You wouldn't happen to have an aspirin? Do you?
- Prone to headaches marshal.

126
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:08,769
Sometimes, but today...

127
00:12:08,769 --> 00:12:11,980
- I'm a little more prone to seasickness.
- Ah, Dehydration...

128
00:12:11,980 --> 00:12:13,649
- You alright boss?
- Yes.

129
00:12:13,649 --> 00:12:16,777
In that case you're quite right.
The simpler the better.

130
00:12:16,777 --> 00:12:18,445
Thank you so much.

131
00:12:18,737 --> 00:12:22,825
Rachel still believes
her children are alive.

132
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:27,496
She also believes this place is her home
in the Berckshires.

133
00:12:27,621 --> 00:12:28,664
You're kidding me.

134
00:12:28,664 --> 00:12:31,834
She's never once in two years acknowledged
that she is in an institution.

135
00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:33,252
She believes we're all...

136
00:12:33,252 --> 00:12:35,754
deliveryman, milkman, postal workers.

137
00:12:35,754 --> 00:12:40,384
To sustain the illusion that her children never died,
she's created an elaborate fictional structure.

138
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:44,638
She gives us all parts to play in that fiction.

139
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:49,143
- So have you searched the grounds yet?
- The warden and his men scoured the island,

140
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:50,352
not a trace.

141
00:12:51,395 --> 00:12:55,983
What's more disturbing is, we don't know
how she got out of her room.

142
00:12:55,983 --> 00:12:58,360
It was locked from the outside

143
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:01,196
and the only window is barred.

144
00:13:02,865 --> 00:13:07,870
It's as if she evaporated straight
through the walls.

145
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:16,003
Brought her right back here after
group therapy, locked her in

146
00:13:16,003 --> 00:13:20,591
I came back for a midnight round
and she was gone.

147
00:13:25,637 --> 00:13:29,975
Seriously doctor, how is it possible
that the truth never gets through to her?

148
00:13:30,017 --> 00:13:33,062
I mean, she's in a
mental institution, right?

149
00:13:33,062 --> 00:13:35,147
Seems like something you'd
notice from time to time.

150
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:38,776
- How many pairs of shoes are the patients given?
- Two pairs.

151
00:13:38,776 --> 00:13:40,986
Sanity is not a choice, marshal,

152
00:13:40,986 --> 00:13:43,781
You can't just choose to get over it.

153
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:46,450
So... she left here barefoot?

154
00:13:47,743 --> 00:13:51,955
Come on Doc, she couldn't get ten
yards in that terrain.

155
00:13:51,955 --> 00:13:52,790
Marshal?

156
00:14:12,059 --> 00:14:14,228
Well this is definitely Rachel's
handwriting.

157
00:14:14,228 --> 00:14:18,857
- I have no idea what the "law of 4" is, though.
- It's not a psychiatric term?

158
00:14:18,857 --> 00:14:20,109
I'm afraid not.

159
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:21,068
Who's 67?

160
00:14:22,861 --> 00:14:24,029
Fuck if I know!

161
00:14:24,029 --> 00:14:27,366
I'd have to say that's quite
close to my clinical conclusion.

162
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:29,868
So you think it's
random scribblings?

163
00:14:29,868 --> 00:14:33,831
Oh no, not at all. Rachel is smart.
Brilliant in fact.

164
00:14:33,831 --> 00:14:36,959
- This paper could be important.
- Excuse me Doctor, but...

165
00:14:36,959 --> 00:14:40,796
- We're gonna have to hold onto this.
- Of course.

166
00:14:41,463 --> 00:14:44,466
And you say she had to come through here.

167
00:14:44,466 --> 00:14:48,512
After lights out, the orderlies play
cards in here.

168
00:14:48,512 --> 00:14:53,726
Last night there were 7 men sitting
at the base of those stairs playing stud poker.

169
00:14:53,726 --> 00:14:57,521
Yet somehow, Rachel managed
to slip past them.

170
00:14:57,521 --> 00:14:57,980
Why?

171
00:14:59,481 --> 00:15:01,817
How? She turns invisible?

172
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:05,404
Doctor, we're gonna need access to personnel files
of all the medical staff.

173
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:07,364
The nurses, the guards, the orderlies.

174
00:15:07,364 --> 00:15:10,868
- Anyone who was working then.
- We'll take your request under consideration.

175
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:13,662
This is not a request, Doctor.

176
00:15:13,912 --> 00:15:16,457
This is a federal facility
and a dangerous prisoner...

177
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:18,542
- Patient.
- Patient...

178
00:15:18,834 --> 00:15:23,297
- has escaped now. You will comply...
- All I can say is that I will see what I can do.

179
00:15:23,297 --> 00:15:28,719
Doctor, we're gonna need to speak with the staff,
do you understand?

180
00:15:28,719 --> 00:15:31,972
I'll assemble them in the
common room after dinner.

181
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:39,730
If you have any further questions feel
free to join the deputy warden in the search.

182
00:15:48,947 --> 00:15:52,409
It's 11 miles to the nearest land
and the water is freezing.

183
00:15:52,409 --> 00:15:55,621
The current was strong last night.
The tide pushing in.

184
00:15:55,621 --> 00:16:03,337
She'd have drowned or been crushed on the
rocks, and her body would have washed back up onshore.

185
00:16:03,337 --> 00:16:06,590
What about those caves down there,
have you checked them?

186
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:09,176
No way she could get there.

187
00:16:09,259 --> 00:16:13,347
The base of those cliffs are covered
in poison ivy, live oak, sumac

188
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:16,892
and a thousand plants with thorns
as big as my dick.

189
00:16:16,892 --> 00:16:21,563
You said it yourself marshal,
she's got no shoes.

190
00:16:25,359 --> 00:16:29,571
All right!
Let's check the other side!

191
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:37,121
- What's that tower?
- It's an old lighthouse.

192
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:40,708
The guards already searched inside it.

193
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:46,422
- What's in there? More patients?
- Sewage treatment facility.

194
00:16:46,422 --> 00:16:48,424
It's getting dark soon.

195
00:16:48,841 --> 00:16:50,592
I'm calling this off for the night.

196
00:16:50,592 --> 00:16:52,052
Let's go, boys!

197
00:16:56,348 --> 00:16:58,559
- You were on watch on the landing, huh?
- Yeah.

198
00:16:58,559 --> 00:17:03,439
Can't nobody get in or out of their room
in that corridor without me seeing.

199
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:05,316
Okay, Rachel Solando,

200
00:17:05,316 --> 00:17:09,862
who else does she have to pass
to get down here?

201
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:14,617
Me.

202
00:17:15,951 --> 00:17:16,910
Glen Miga.

203
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:22,291
- Sir, I didn't see nothing.
- And you were at your post all night?

204
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:24,501
Yes. But I didn't see a thing.

205
00:17:26,962 --> 00:17:27,588
Glen.

206
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:30,549
Glen.

207
00:17:33,469 --> 00:17:35,220
Tell me the truth.

208
00:17:39,808 --> 00:17:42,227
I maybe... went to the bathroom.

209
00:17:42,227 --> 00:17:47,942
- What? You breached protocol? Christ...
- I wasn't gone more than a minute.

210
00:17:47,942 --> 00:17:50,778
All right, let's back up here.
Let's all just back up.

211
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:54,323
Miss Solando was put in
her room for lights out.

212
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:57,451
Does anybody here know
what she did before that?

213
00:17:57,451 --> 00:17:58,160
Anyone?

214
00:17:59,954 --> 00:18:02,748
Come on. Anyone. Anyone. Anyone.

215
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:06,418
She was in a group therapy session.

216
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:09,546
Huh. Did anything unusual occur?

217
00:18:09,546 --> 00:18:11,215
Define "unusual".

218
00:18:11,966 --> 00:18:15,219
- Excuse me.
- It's a mental institution, marshal.

219
00:18:15,219 --> 00:18:17,221
For criminally insane.

220
00:18:17,304 --> 00:18:20,849
"Usual", isn't a big part of our day.

221
00:18:21,267 --> 00:18:22,768
I will rephrase.

222
00:18:23,269 --> 00:18:27,106
Did anything happen last night
during group therapy, that was more...

223
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:30,234
- let's say, more memorable than...
- Normal?

224
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:30,985
Exactly!

225
00:18:31,819 --> 00:18:33,237
No. I'm sorry.

226
00:18:34,196 --> 00:18:38,450
Did Mrs. Solando say anything
during group therapy?

227
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:41,328
She was worried about the rain.

228
00:18:41,579 --> 00:18:43,789
And she hated the food here.

229
00:18:43,789 --> 00:18:47,710
Complained constantly.
Last night included.

230
00:18:48,377 --> 00:18:51,922
So... you were there.
Was there a doctor present?

231
00:18:51,922 --> 00:18:54,216
Yes. Dr. Sheehan led the discussion.

232
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:56,802
Dr. Sheehan?

233
00:18:58,178 --> 00:19:01,181
Yes. He was running the session.

234
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:03,601
He's Rachels's "primary".

235
00:19:03,601 --> 00:19:08,105
The psychaiatrist who directly
oversees her care.

236
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:11,025
We're gonna need to speak with Dr. Sheehan.

237
00:19:11,025 --> 00:19:13,611
I'm afraid that won't be possible.

238
00:19:13,611 --> 00:19:16,989
He left on the ferry this morning.
His vacation was already planned.

239
00:19:16,989 --> 00:19:18,908
He'd putting it off too long.

240
00:19:18,908 --> 00:19:21,327
