494
00:38:50,205 --> 00:38:51,581
Andrew Laeddis,

495
00:38:52,832 --> 00:38:57,587
was the maintenance man in the apartment
building where my wife and I lived.

496
00:38:58,463 --> 00:38:59,172
Okay.

497
00:39:01,591 --> 00:39:03,718
He was also a firebug.

498
00:39:06,387 --> 00:39:09,057
Andrew Laeddis lit the match,

499
00:39:11,726 --> 00:39:15,563
that caused the fire that killed my wife.

500
00:39:22,737 --> 00:39:23,613
Let 'em out!

501
00:39:26,783 --> 00:39:28,868
What happened to Laeddis?

502
00:39:28,868 --> 00:39:32,872
Got away with it.
Laeddis got away with it and disappeared.

503
00:39:33,373 --> 00:39:35,667
About a year ago, I opened up the
newspaper and there he is.

504
00:39:35,667 --> 00:39:37,836
He's an ugly looking son of a bitch.

505
00:39:37,836 --> 00:39:40,463
He had a new scar from his right temple
down to his left lip.

506
00:39:40,463 --> 00:39:43,883
Eyes different colors.
Not the type of face you forget.

507
00:39:43,883 --> 00:39:47,053
He'd burned down a schoolhouse. Killed 2 people.

508
00:39:47,053 --> 00:39:48,972
He said voices told him to do it.

509
00:39:48,972 --> 00:39:51,683
First he was sent to prison
and then he was transferred here.

510
00:39:51,683 --> 00:39:53,852
- Then what?
- Then, nothing.

511
00:39:53,852 --> 00:39:57,814
He vanished like he never existed.
No record whatsoever.

512
00:39:57,814 --> 00:40:00,483
I'm sure he's not in ward B
that leaves ward C.

513
00:40:00,483 --> 00:40:01,693
Or he could be dead.

514
00:40:01,693 --> 00:40:07,282
So could Rachel Solando for that matter.
Lot of places to hide a body here.

515
00:40:07,824 --> 00:40:11,619
Only one place
no one really knows.

516
00:40:22,172 --> 00:40:26,217
That patient, Bridget Kearne,
when she sent me for water,

517
00:40:26,217 --> 00:40:29,262
she said something to you back there, didn't she?

518
00:40:29,262 --> 00:40:29,596
No.

519
00:40:32,432 --> 00:40:33,725
Come on boss!

520
00:40:37,353 --> 00:40:38,646
She wrote it.

521
00:40:54,245 --> 00:40:54,746
Boss!

522
00:40:55,997 --> 00:40:59,667
We gotta get indoors. It's turning
into fucking Kansas out here...

523
00:40:59,667 --> 00:41:02,170
- All right.
- Now. Let's go!

524
00:41:04,631 --> 00:41:05,632
Watch out!

525
00:41:08,384 --> 00:41:08,968
Jesus!

526
00:41:11,513 --> 00:41:13,765
Come on! Let's go back!

527
00:41:31,199 --> 00:41:33,326
Jesus Christ!
Damn it!

528
00:41:44,337 --> 00:41:48,591
- Are you okay boss?
- Yes. That's all right.

529
00:41:54,180 --> 00:41:57,016
So... if Laeddis is here...

530
00:41:57,016 --> 00:41:59,894
What are you going to do boss?

531
00:42:01,479 --> 00:42:04,274
I'm not here to kill Leaddis.

532
00:42:11,656 --> 00:42:15,452
If it was my wife
I'd kill him twice.

533
00:42:25,211 --> 00:42:31,426
When we got through the gates of Dakau,
the SS guards surrendered.

534
00:42:38,308 --> 00:42:43,730
The commandante tried to kill himself
before we got there...

535
00:42:45,190 --> 00:42:46,858
but he botched it.

536
00:42:48,026 --> 00:42:50,278
Took him an hour to die.

537
00:42:54,783 --> 00:42:59,329
When I went outside,
I saw all the bodies on the ground.

538
00:43:03,083 --> 00:43:04,751
Too many to count.

539
00:43:31,611 --> 00:43:33,530
Too many to imagine.

540
00:43:36,199 --> 00:43:36,950
So yeah

541
00:43:39,953 --> 00:43:45,583
The guards surrendered, we took
their guns, we lined them up...

542
00:44:27,959 --> 00:44:29,627
It wasn't warfare,

543
00:44:32,005 --> 00:44:33,340
it was murder.

544
00:44:37,719 --> 00:44:39,763
Yeah I've had enough of killing.

545
00:44:42,599 --> 00:44:44,934
That's not why I'm here.

546
00:44:45,518 --> 00:44:47,854
So what is this all about?

547
00:44:49,898 --> 00:44:51,983
After Laeddis vanished,

548
00:44:52,942 --> 00:44:57,030
I started doing some checking
on Ashecliffe.

549
00:44:57,113 --> 00:45:02,160
A lot of people knew about this place, but no
one wants to talk...

550
00:45:02,160 --> 00:45:05,163
You know? It's like they're scared of something.

551
00:45:06,039 --> 00:45:09,876
You know this place is funded by
a special grant

552
00:45:09,876 --> 00:45:13,088
from the House of
Unamerican Activities Committee.

553
00:45:13,088 --> 00:45:19,260
HUAC. And how exactly are we fighting
the Commies from an island in Boston Harbor?

554
00:45:19,260 --> 00:45:22,639
By conducting experiments on the mind.

555
00:45:23,223 --> 00:45:24,724
At least that's my guess.

556
00:45:24,724 --> 00:45:26,726
And you think thats going on in here?

557
00:45:26,726 --> 00:45:29,020
Like I said, no one would talk, right?

558
00:45:29,020 --> 00:45:31,856
Until I found someone
who used to be a patient here.

559
00:45:31,856 --> 00:45:33,733
Guy's name is George Noyce.

560
00:45:33,733 --> 00:45:36,361
Nice college kid.
Socialist.

561
00:45:36,569 --> 00:45:40,073
He gets offered some money to do a
psych study. Guess what they were testing?

562
00:45:40,073 --> 00:45:43,410
- Tooth paste?
- So he starts seeing dragons everywhere.

563
00:45:43,410 --> 00:45:47,539
Almost beats his professor to death
Ends up here in Ashecliffe.

564
00:45:48,331 --> 00:45:49,040
Ward C.

565
00:45:49,332 --> 00:45:52,752
They released him after 1 year, right?
What does he do?

566
00:45:52,752 --> 00:45:58,550
Two weeks on the mainland he walks into
a bar and stabs three men to death.

567
00:45:58,550 --> 00:46:01,428
His lawyer pleads insanity,
but Noyce...

568
00:46:01,428 --> 00:46:03,596
Noyce, he stands up in the courtroom and

569
00:46:03,596 --> 00:46:05,473
he begs the judge,
for the electric chair.

570
00:46:05,473 --> 00:46:08,393
Anywhere but a mental hospital.

571
00:46:08,393 --> 00:46:12,147
Judge gives him life in Dedham prison.

572
00:46:12,147 --> 00:46:16,276
- And you found him?
- Yeah, I found him.

573
00:46:16,276 --> 00:46:17,444
Well, he's a mess

574
00:46:19,404 --> 00:46:22,324
- But it's pretty clear from what he tells me, ...
- What?

575
00:46:22,324 --> 00:46:25,327
... they're experimenting on people here.

576
00:46:25,327 --> 00:46:27,287
I don't know, boss.

577
00:46:28,872 --> 00:46:31,583
- How do you believe a crazy guy?
- That's the beauty of it isn't it?

578
00:46:31,583 --> 00:46:36,296
Crazy people are perfect subjects.
They talk, but nobody listens.

579
00:46:36,296 --> 00:46:38,006
I stood in Dakau.

580
00:46:38,048 --> 00:46:43,219
We saw what human beings are capable
of doing to each other, right?

581
00:46:43,428 --> 00:46:45,513
For Christ sake we fought a goddamn war

582
00:46:45,513 --> 00:46:47,974
to stop them, and now
I find out it may be happening here?

583
00:46:47,974 --> 00:46:50,810
On our soil?
No.

584
00:46:51,895 --> 00:46:54,898
So what are you really here to do, Teddy?

585
00:46:54,898 --> 00:46:57,442
I'm gonna get the proof,

586
00:46:57,442 --> 00:47:01,696
I'm gonna go back, and blow
the lid off this place.

587
00:47:01,696 --> 00:47:02,614
That's it.

588
00:47:03,657 --> 00:47:05,033
Wait a minute.

589
00:47:06,243 --> 00:47:08,954
You started asking around about Ashecliffe.

590
00:47:08,954 --> 00:47:14,251
Waiting for a chance to get out here
then suddenly they need a US marshal?

591
00:47:14,251 --> 00:47:17,128
I got lucky. There was a patient escape,
it was the perfect excuse.

592
00:47:17,128 --> 00:47:20,215
No, no, no boss.
Luck doesn't work that way.

593
00:47:20,215 --> 00:47:24,928
The world doesn't work that way. They got an
electrified fence around a septic facility.

594
00:47:24,928 --> 00:47:28,181
Ward C is inside a Civil War fort?

595
00:47:28,515 --> 00:47:32,686
A chief of staff with ties to the OSS
Funding from HUAC?

596
00:47:32,686 --> 00:47:36,856
Jesus Christ! Everything about this place
stinks of "government ops".

597
00:47:36,856 --> 00:47:38,942
- What If they wanted you here?
- Bullshit.

598
00:47:38,942 --> 00:47:40,819
- You were asking questions.
- Bullshit.

599
00:47:40,819 --> 00:47:46,157
Bullshit? We came in for Rachel Solando? Where is
one shred of evidence that she even existed?

600
00:47:46,157 --> 00:47:48,618
There's no way they could of known I'd be
assigned to this case. No way...

601
00:47:48,618 --> 00:47:51,621
While you were looking into them,
they were looking into you.

602
00:47:51,621 --> 00:47:54,291
All they need to do
is fake an escape to get you here.

603
00:47:54,291 --> 00:47:59,254
And now they have you.
Now they have us both, here, now.

604
00:48:01,965 --> 00:48:03,383
Marshal, are you out here?

605
00:48:04,467 --> 00:48:06,636
This is deputy warden McPherson.

606
00:48:07,429 --> 00:48:08,138
Marshal!

607
00:48:08,513 --> 00:48:10,056
How about that? They found us huh.

608
00:48:10,056 --> 00:48:13,393
It's an island, boss. They're always gonna find us.

609
00:48:14,728 --> 00:48:15,854
I know you are in there...

610
00:48:17,689 --> 00:48:20,066
We're getting off of this Goddamned island.
You and me.

611
00:48:20,567 --> 00:48:21,526
Come on!

612
00:48:25,530 --> 00:48:27,115
- Come on!
- Go!

613
00:48:37,125 --> 00:48:40,212
Get dried off.
Dr. Cawley wants to talk to you. Now!

614
00:48:41,004 --> 00:48:43,965
And hurry up, this thing is turning
into a goddamn hurricane!

615
00:48:49,596 --> 00:48:51,097
I dropped those suits off to be cleaned.

616
00:48:52,057 --> 00:48:53,141
It should be ready by tomorrow.

617
00:48:54,100 --> 00:48:55,685
That is if we don't all wash away first.

618
00:48:56,853 --> 00:49:00,941
Speaking of which, I'm afraid your smokes were
pretty much done for.

619
00:49:01,691 --> 00:49:02,567
So...

620
00:49:04,736 --> 00:49:06,112
This is our only choice, huh?

621
00:49:06,947 --> 00:49:09,908
Got something really nice in prison already
if that don't work for you...

622
00:49:10,200 --> 00:49:12,369
Now that you mention it, these are just fine.

623
00:49:13,828 --> 00:49:17,040
That's why I must repeat my insistence
that all ward C patients

624
00:49:17,040 --> 00:49:18,375
be placed in manual restraints.

625
00:49:19,251 --> 00:49:22,504
If the facility floods, they'll drown.
You know that.

626
00:49:23,004 --> 00:49:25,382
- That would take a lot of flooding.
- We are on an island,

627
00:49:25,507 --> 00:49:26,967
in the middle of the ocean,
during a hurricane.

628
00:49:27,300 --> 00:49:29,594
A lot of flooding seems like a
distinct possibility.

629
00:49:29,594 --> 00:49:32,347
It's a gamble, Steven.
Say the power fails, ...

630
00:49:32,597 --> 00:49:33,557
There's a backup generator.

631
00:49:33,807 --> 00:49:36,226
And if that goes? The cell doors
will open.

632
00:49:37,769 --> 00:49:39,312
Where are they going to go?

633
00:49:40,230 --> 00:49:43,358
They can't just hop a ferry, scoot over
to the mainland and wreak havoc.

634
00:49:43,358 --> 00:49:47,487
You're quite right. They're far more likely
to wreak havoc right here on us.

635
00:49:48,488 --> 00:49:50,282
If they're manacled to the floor, they'll die.

636
00:49:51,700 --> 00:49:53,034
That's 24 human beings.

637
00:49:53,910 --> 00:49:55,745
You can live with that, can you?

638
00:49:55,954 --> 00:49:57,539
Frankly, if it were up to me,

639
00:49:57,831 --> 00:50:01,209
I'd put all 42 in wards A and B in
manual restraints as well.

640
00:50:01,334 --> 00:50:02,169
Excuse me
Excuse me

641
00:50:03,170 --> 00:50:06,840
- Marshal.
- I'm sorry doctor, I just have one quick question.

642
00:50:06,840 --> 00:50:08,133
Yes, I will be with you in a moment.

643
00:50:08,133 --> 00:50:10,927
We spoke this morning
about Rachel Solando's note.

644
00:50:11,094 --> 00:50:12,762
The law of 4, I loved that.

645
00:50:12,762 --> 00:50:16,391
You said you had no idea what
that second line could refer to. Correct?

646
00:50:17,434 --> 00:50:18,602
Who is 67?

647
00:50:18,602 --> 00:50:22,355
Yes, I'm afraid I still don't.
None of us do.

648
00:50:22,355 --> 00:50:24,441
Uh huh. Nothing comes to mind.

649
00:50:27,277 --> 00:50:28,028
Nothing?

650
00:50:32,449 --> 00:50:34,326
Because I believe I just heard
you say there are

651
00:50:34,326 --> 00:50:37,037
24 patients in ward C.

652
00:50:37,746 --> 00:50:40,332
And 42 of patients, in wards A and B

653
00:50:40,540 --> 00:50:43,960
Which means there is a total of what?
66 patients here in this facility.

654
00:50:45,253 --> 00:50:46,588
That is correct, yes.

655
00:50:49,883 --> 00:50:52,552
Then it seems that
Rachel Solando was suggesting

656
00:50:53,053 --> 00:50:56,306
that you have a 67th patient, doctor.

657
00:50:57,432 --> 00:51:00,769
- But I'm afraid we don't.
- This is ridiculous.

658
00:51:00,769 --> 00:51:03,313
- What are you doing here?
- We are doing our goddamn job.

659
00:51:04,105 --> 00:51:06,483
Didn't McPherson tell you the good news?

660
00:51:07,776 --> 00:51:09,444
No, what's the good news, doctor?

661
00:51:10,445 --> 00:51:11,822
Rachel has been found.

662
00:51:13,323 --> 00:51:14,282
She's here.

663
00:51:15,992 --> 00:51:17,035
Safe and sound.

664
00:51:29,256 --> 00:51:30,340
There is not a mark on her.

665
00:51:34,845 --> 00:51:35,846
Who are these men?

666
00:51:39,433 --> 00:51:40,851
Why are they in my house?

667
00:51:41,351 --> 00:51:42,769
Police officers, Rachel.

668
00:51:43,103 --> 00:51:45,439
They... have a few questions.

669
00:51:49,401 --> 00:51:50,110
Ma'am.

670
00:51:53,363 --> 00:51:56,533
There's been a sighting of a known
Communist

671
00:51:56,533 --> 00:51:59,995
subversive in this area
passing out literature

672
00:52:01,997 --> 00:52:03,373
Here?

673
00:52:05,542 --> 00:52:06,960
In this neighborhood?

674
00:52:07,502 --> 00:52:08,670
Yes, I'm afraid so.

675
00:52:10,297 --> 00:52:13,759
Now, if you can tell us what you did
yesterday, where you were,

676
00:52:14,426 --> 00:52:15,969
it would really help us narrow our search.

677
00:52:17,971 --> 00:52:18,597
Yes...

678
00:52:21,975 --> 00:52:22,976
Well, I...umm

679
00:52:26,605 --> 00:52:30,567
I made breakfast for Jim
and the children,

680
00:52:30,859 --> 00:52:32,110
and then I...

681
00:52:34,362 --> 00:52:37,616
I packed Jim's lunch
and he left.

682
00:52:40,118 --> 00:52:43,789
Then I sent the children off to school.

683
00:52:47,292 --> 00:52:48,335
And then...

684
00:52:54,966 --> 00:52:58,970
I decided to take a long swim in the lake.

685
00:53:04,976 --> 00:53:05,769
I see...

686
00:53:10,065 --> 00:53:11,525
And after that?

687
00:53:19,533 --> 00:53:20,742
After that...

688
00:53:30,335 --> 00:53:32,003
I thought of you.

689
00:53:38,218 --> 00:53:39,761
I... I'm sorry, ma'am.

690
00:53:39,761 --> 00:53:43,265
I don't know what you're talking about.

691
00:53:45,308 --> 00:53:49,229
Don't you know how lonely I've been, Jim?

692
00:53:54,067 --> 00:53:55,402
You're gone...

693
00:53:59,364 --> 00:54:00,574
You're dead.

694
00:54:05,704 --> 00:54:08,498
I cry every night.

695
00:54:13,587 --> 00:54:16,340
How am I supposed to survive?

696
00:54:18,383 --> 00:54:18,800
God.

697
00:54:29,311 --> 00:54:32,230
Rachel... it will be all right.

698
00:54:35,650 --> 00:54:37,611
I'm so sorry, but...

699
00:54:39,112 --> 00:54:42,324
everything is gonna be all right? Okay?

700
00:54:43,950 --> 00:54:45,160
I buried you.

701
00:54:47,496 --> 00:54:52,501
I buried an empty casket. Your body
rained down lumps of flesh splashing

702
00:54:52,501 --> 00:54:54,002
into the sea eaten by sharks.

703
00:54:58,131 --> 00:55:02,052
My Jim is dead,
So who the fuck are you?

704
00:55:04,137 --> 00:55:06,181
Who the fuck are you?!

705
00:55:06,765 --> 00:55:09,184
Who are you?! Who are you?!

706
00:55:19,111 --> 00:55:20,904
I'm sorry about that.

707
00:55:20,904 --> 00:55:24,324
I didn't want to interrupt, I thought
she might tell you something, but...

708
00:55:24,324 --> 00:55:26,451
we found her down by the lighthouse,

709
00:55:26,451 --> 00:55:27,911
skipping stones.

710
00:55:29,329 --> 00:55:33,041
We have no idea how she got out there. I'm going
to ask you both to go down into basement.

711
00:55:33,041 --> 00:55:37,212
There's food, water, and cots.
It's the safest place to be

712
00:55:37,212 --> 00:55:39,423
when the hurricane hits.

713
00:55:42,968 --> 00:55:45,053
Are you all right?
You look pale.

714
00:55:45,053 --> 00:55:47,222
I'm fine, it's just uh...

715
00:55:48,223 --> 00:55:50,058
Boss, are you okay?

716
00:55:51,018 --> 00:55:53,437
It's just so Goddamn bright? Isn't it?

717
00:55:53,437 --> 00:55:58,108
Photo sensitivity, headaches sometimes?
Marshal are you having a migraine?

718
00:55:58,108 --> 00:55:59,234
I'll be alright.

719
00:56:07,367 --> 00:56:10,954
- What's wrong with him.
- Take these, marshal. You'll sleep a couple of hours, wake up clear as a bell.

720
00:56:10,954 --> 00:56:13,415
He's having a migraine.
Imagine someone sawed open your head and

721
00:56:13,415 --> 00:56:15,542
filled it with razors then shook it
as hard as they could.

722
00:56:15,542 --> 00:56:17,085
Take the pills, marshal.

723
00:56:17,085 --> 00:56:21,965
- No... I don't want the pills.
- It'll stop the pain. Take the pills.

724
00:56:25,594 --> 00:56:27,846
He's going to need to lie down.

725
00:56:33,352 --> 00:56:34,102
Oh God!

726
00:56:49,618 --> 00:56:51,453
Careful. All right.

727
00:56:52,829 --> 00:56:54,831
Gonna be okay. Relax.

728
00:57:01,672 --> 00:57:03,632
- Who is that?
- Him?

729
00:57:04,591 --> 00:57:06,301
That's the warden.

730
00:57:08,303 --> 00:57:11,390
Don't you worry about him, alright?

731
00:57:16,937 --> 00:57:19,606
Looks like an ex-military prick.

732
00:57:20,399 --> 00:57:24,278
You know what? I ain't gonna argue
with you on that one.

733
00:58:48,904 --> 00:58:51,281
You should have saved me.

734
00:58:53,283 --> 00:58:56,328
You should have saved all of us.

735
00:59:25,440 --> 00:59:26,567
Hey buddy.

736
00:59:28,652 --> 00:59:29,403
Hey.

737
00:59:29,903 --> 00:59:30,654
Laeddis.

738
00:59:32,823 --> 00:59:34,199
Yes.

739
00:59:45,002 --> 00:59:46,003
Hi, buddy.

740
00:59:47,421 --> 00:59:49,631
No hard feelings, right?

741
00:59:56,054 --> 00:59:57,639
No hard feelings.

