And before I was a patient
in Ashecliff, I worked here.

1005
01:24:34,534 --> 01:24:35,952
You were a nurse?

1006
01:24:37,662 --> 01:24:39,372
I was a doctor, marshal.

1007
01:24:43,334 --> 01:24:44,585
You think I'm crazy?

1008
01:24:45,086 --> 01:24:47,922
- No, I ...
- And if I say I'm not crazy ...

1009
01:24:48,423 --> 01:24:51,342
well that hardly helps, does it?

1010
01:24:52,593 --> 01:24:56,055
That's the Kafkaesque genius of it.

1011
01:24:59,058 --> 01:25:00,351
People tell the world you're crazy

1012
01:25:01,144 --> 01:25:02,520
and all your protests to the contrary,

1013
01:25:03,021 --> 01:25:04,230
just confirms what they're saying.

1014
01:25:07,400 --> 01:25:09,569
I'm not following you.
I'm sorry.

1015
01:25:09,777 --> 01:25:11,195
Once you are declared insane,

1016
01:25:12,071 --> 01:25:14,824
then anything you do is called
a part of that insanity.

1017
01:25:14,824 --> 01:25:17,660
Your reasonable protests
or denial.

1018
01:25:18,661 --> 01:25:20,872
Valid fears,
paranoia.

1019
01:25:20,872 --> 01:25:23,124
Survival instincts.

1020
01:25:23,666 --> 01:25:24,751
Defense mechanisms.

1021
01:25:25,460 --> 01:25:28,212
You're smarter than you look marshal.
That's probably not a good thing.

1022
01:25:29,797 --> 01:25:30,798
Tell me something...

1023
01:25:30,965 --> 01:25:32,175
Yeah...

1024
01:25:34,093 --> 01:25:35,845
What happened to you?

1025
01:25:36,596 --> 01:25:39,432
I started asking about these large
shipments of sodium-anatol

1026
01:25:40,224 --> 01:25:43,394
- and opium-based hallucinogens.
- Psychotropic drugs.

1027
01:25:44,854 --> 01:25:46,272
I asked about the surgeries, too.

1028
01:25:49,609 --> 01:25:51,361
Ever heard of trans-orbital lobotomy?

1029
01:25:52,987 --> 01:25:54,697
They zap the patient with electroshocks,

1030
01:25:55,782 --> 01:25:59,827
then go through the eye with an ice pick

1031
01:26:00,787 --> 01:26:02,538
and pull out some nerve fibers.

1032
01:26:05,583 --> 01:26:07,043
Makes the patients much more obedient.

1033
01:26:07,919 --> 01:26:09,963
Tractable.

1034
01:26:10,713 --> 01:26:11,798
It's barbaric.

1035
01:26:13,216 --> 01:26:14,384
Unconscionable.

1036
01:26:15,593 --> 01:26:20,390
Do you know how pain enters the
body marshal? Do you?

1037
01:26:21,140 --> 01:26:22,642
Depends on where you're hurt.

1038
01:26:23,518 --> 01:26:24,936
No, it has nothing to do with the flesh.

1039
01:26:25,186 --> 01:26:26,938
The brain controls pain.

1040
01:26:28,022 --> 01:26:32,277
The brain controls fear, empathy,
sleep, hunger, anger... everything.

1041
01:26:34,821 --> 01:26:35,989
What If you could control it?

1042
01:26:37,156 --> 01:26:38,283
The brain?

1043
01:26:38,324 --> 01:26:39,993
Re-create a man,

1044
01:26:40,785 --> 01:26:42,579
so he doesn't feel pain,

1045
01:26:43,121 --> 01:26:45,331
or love, or sympathy.

1046
01:26:46,916 --> 01:26:51,337
A man who can't be interrogated
because he has no memories to confess.

1047
01:26:53,881 --> 01:26:55,967
You can never take away
all a man's memories.

1048
01:26:56,092 --> 01:26:57,468
Never.

1049
01:26:57,677 --> 01:27:01,222
Marshal, the North Koreans
used American POWs

1050
01:27:01,723 --> 01:27:03,182
during their brainwashing experiments.

1051
01:27:03,474 --> 01:27:06,394
They turned soldiers into traitors.
That's what they are doing here.

1052
01:27:07,145 --> 01:27:11,816
They're creating ghosts to go out in the world.
And do things sane men never do.

1053
01:27:11,816 --> 01:27:14,736
To have that kind of ability, that kind of knowledge.

1054
01:27:15,236 --> 01:27:16,821
That would take years.

1055
01:27:17,030 --> 01:27:20,617
Years of research,
hundreds of patients to experiment on.

1056
01:27:22,577 --> 01:27:24,996
50 years from now,
people will look back

1057
01:27:25,079 --> 01:27:27,832
and say, "Here. This place
is where it all began."

1058
01:27:29,250 --> 01:27:30,376
The Nazis used the Jews.

1059
01:27:30,668 --> 01:27:34,505
The Soviets used prisoners
in their own gulags, and we...

1060
01:27:34,881 --> 01:27:36,299
We tested patients,

1061
01:27:37,091 --> 01:27:38,259
on Shutter Island.

1062
01:27:39,552 --> 01:27:42,805
No, they won't ...
No

1063
01:27:46,017 --> 01:27:47,227
You do understand

1064
01:27:50,939 --> 01:27:53,107
That they can't let you leave?

1065
01:27:53,566 --> 01:27:54,651
I am a federal marshal ...

1066
01:27:55,401 --> 01:27:56,819
They can't stop me.

1067
01:27:58,238 --> 01:27:59,447
I was an esteemed psychiatrist,

1068
01:28:01,574 --> 01:28:04,035
from a respected family.

1069
01:28:04,994 --> 01:28:06,663
It didn't matter.

1070
01:28:09,332 --> 01:28:10,375
Let me ask you ...

1071
01:28:11,084 --> 01:28:12,835
any past traumas in your life?

1072
01:28:14,337 --> 01:28:19,217
Yes. Why? Why would that matter?

1073
01:28:19,509 --> 01:28:21,511
Because they can point to some
event in your past and say

1074
01:28:21,511 --> 01:28:24,097
it is the reason you lost your sanity

1075
01:28:24,430 --> 01:28:26,474
So that when they commit you here

1076
01:28:27,016 --> 01:28:30,937
your friends and colleagues will say,
"Of course he cracked."

1077
01:28:32,772 --> 01:28:34,190
"And who wouldn't have,
after what he'd been through."

1078
01:28:34,190 --> 01:28:35,567
They can say that about anyone

1079
01:28:35,817 --> 01:28:38,945
- anyone at all.
- The point is they're going to say it about you.

1080
01:28:42,615 --> 01:28:44,742
How's your head?

1081
01:28:45,785 --> 01:28:48,538
- My head?
- Any funny dreams lately?

1082
01:28:49,122 --> 01:28:53,459
Trouble sleeping? Headaches?

1083
01:28:54,836 --> 01:28:56,671
I am prone to migraines. Yes.

1084
01:28:56,671 --> 01:28:57,714
Jesus!

1085
01:29:00,425 --> 01:29:02,051
You haven't taken any pills, have you?

1086
01:29:02,886 --> 01:29:05,346
- I mean even aspirin?
- They hit the aspirin?

1087
01:29:05,346 --> 01:29:06,973
Jesus!

1088
01:29:07,182 --> 01:29:10,560
And you ate the food in the cafeteria and drank
coffee they gave you.

1089
01:29:10,894 --> 01:29:13,229
You tell me at least that
you've been smoking your own cigarettes.

1090
01:29:15,815 --> 01:29:18,860
No... no.

1091
01:29:20,195 --> 01:29:21,529
No. I haven't.

1092
01:29:21,779 --> 01:29:24,449
It takes 36 to 48 hours for
neuroleptic narcotics

1093
01:29:24,532 --> 01:29:28,786
to reach workable levels in
the blood stream.

1094
01:29:28,786 --> 01:29:30,705
Palsy comes first

1095
01:29:31,706 --> 01:29:33,875
First the fingertips and then
eventually the whole hand.

1096
01:29:35,877 --> 01:29:40,215
Seen any walking nightmares
lately, marshal? Huh?

1097
01:29:42,634 --> 01:29:44,469
Tell me what goes on in that lighthouse?

1098
01:29:46,221 --> 01:29:47,388
Tell me.

1099
01:29:48,598 --> 01:29:50,642
Brain surgery.

1100
01:29:51,309 --> 01:29:55,313
"Let's open the skull and see
what happens if we pull on this" kind.

1101
01:29:55,772 --> 01:29:58,191
"We learned it from the Nazi's" kind.

1102
01:30:00,902 --> 01:30:02,737
It's where they create the ghosts.

1103
01:30:04,364 --> 01:30:06,407
Who knows about this?

1104
01:30:06,950 --> 01:30:08,827
On the island I mean. Who?

1105
01:30:11,204 --> 01:30:12,622
Everyone.

1106
01:30:12,705 --> 01:30:16,251
Oh come on. The nurses? The orderlies?

1107
01:30:17,168 --> 01:30:19,754
- They couldn't possibly know...
- Everyone.

1108
01:30:38,648 --> 01:30:40,942
You can't stay here.

1109
01:30:41,359 --> 01:30:44,946
They think I'm dead, that I drowned. I'm afraid
if they come looking for you, they might find me.

1110
01:30:45,864 --> 01:30:47,323
I'm sorry, but you have to go.

1111
01:30:54,706 --> 01:30:56,332
I'm gonna come back for you.

1112
01:30:56,499 --> 01:30:59,544
I won't be here. I move during the day.
new places every night.

1113
01:30:59,544 --> 01:31:01,921
But I could come get you
off of this island.

1114
01:31:01,921 --> 01:31:04,174
Haven't you heard a word I've said?

1115
01:31:04,716 --> 01:31:08,178
The only way off the island
is the ferry and they control it.

1116
01:31:08,678 --> 01:31:10,430
You'll never leave here.

1117
01:31:20,356 --> 01:31:21,775
I had a friend.

1118
01:31:22,233 --> 01:31:24,778
I was with him yesterday,
but we got separated.

1119
01:31:25,445 --> 01:31:27,113
Have you seen him?

1120
01:31:28,364 --> 01:31:30,033
Marshal...

1121
01:31:31,409 --> 01:31:33,286
You have no friends.

1122
01:32:05,944 --> 01:32:08,238
There you are.

1123
01:32:10,073 --> 01:32:12,617
We've been wondering when
you'd show up.

1124
01:32:14,452 --> 01:32:15,912
Have a seat.

1125
01:32:16,454 --> 01:32:17,789
Come on.

1126
01:32:28,717 --> 01:32:31,177
Taking a leisurely stroll? Were we?

1127
01:32:32,303 --> 01:32:33,847
I was just...

1128
01:32:34,556 --> 01:32:35,932
just looking around.

1129
01:32:38,601 --> 01:32:40,770
Did you enjoy
God's latest gift?

1130
01:32:42,355 --> 01:32:44,524
- What?
- God's gift.

1131
01:32:46,025 --> 01:32:47,610
The violence.

1132
01:32:52,449 --> 01:32:56,036
When I came downstairs in my home
and I saw that tree in my living room,

1133
01:32:56,953 --> 01:32:59,122
it reached down for me like a divine hand.

1134
01:33:00,707 --> 01:33:02,500
God loves violence.

1135
01:33:05,587 --> 01:33:08,381
- I hadn't noticed.
- Sure you have.

1136
01:33:08,965 --> 01:33:10,800
Why else would there be so much of it?

1137
01:33:11,551 --> 01:33:13,053
It's in us.

1138
01:33:13,219 --> 01:33:14,512
It's what we are.

1139
01:33:16,264 --> 01:33:19,684
We wage war, we burn sacrifices,
we pillage and plunder

1140
01:33:19,684 --> 01:33:21,353
and tear at the flesh
of our brothers

1141
01:33:21,353 --> 01:33:25,482
and why? Because God gave us violence
to wage in his honor.

1142
01:33:28,651 --> 01:33:30,945
I thought God gave us moral order.

1143
01:33:30,945 --> 01:33:33,782
There is no moral order
as pure as this storm.

1144
01:33:34,574 --> 01:33:36,743
There's no moral order at all.

1145
01:33:37,118 --> 01:33:40,914
There's just this:
can my violence conquer yours?

1146
01:33:46,378 --> 01:33:48,338
- I'm not violent.
- Yes you are.

1147
01:33:49,923 --> 01:33:51,883
You're as violent as they come.

1148
01:33:52,926 --> 01:33:55,887
I know this because I'm as violent as they come.

1149
01:33:56,930 --> 01:33:58,848
With the constraints of society,
we are lifted and

1150
01:33:59,099 --> 01:34:04,312
If I was all that stood between you and a meal, you
would crack my skull with a rock and eat my meaty parts.

1151
01:34:06,940 --> 01:34:08,566
Wouldn't you?

1152
01:34:11,277 --> 01:34:15,240
Cawley thinks you're harmless, that you can be
controlled, but I know different.

1153
01:34:16,282 --> 01:34:20,537
- You don't know me.
- Oh but I do. Oh I know you.

1154
01:34:21,413 --> 01:34:23,665
We've known each other for centuries.

1155
01:34:33,508 --> 01:34:36,261
If I was to sink my teeth into your eye
right now,

1156
01:34:36,261 --> 01:34:39,723
would you be able to stop me before I blinded you?

1157
01:34:43,727 --> 01:34:45,395
Give it a try.

1158
01:34:46,855 --> 01:34:51,234
That's the spirit.

1159
01:35:36,112 --> 01:35:37,697
Where have you been?

1160
01:35:38,823 --> 01:35:41,076
Wandering, just looking at your island.

1161
01:35:41,117 --> 01:35:45,580
Oh I forgot. You're leaving.
Now that Rachel has been found.

1162
01:35:45,914 --> 01:35:47,415
Sure. Yeah.

1163
01:35:49,668 --> 01:35:50,961
Big meeting?

1164
01:35:51,544 --> 01:35:54,130
Oh, yes ...

1165
01:35:54,130 --> 01:35:56,800
Apparently there was an unidentified man
in ward C yesterday

1166
01:35:56,800 --> 01:36:00,428
He subdued a highly dangerous patient.
Quite handily.

1167
01:36:01,554 --> 01:36:02,639
Is that so?

1168
01:36:02,722 --> 01:36:07,477
It seems he had a long conversation with a
paranoid schizophrenic, George Noyce.

1169
01:36:10,438 --> 01:36:13,441
This Noyce,
you said his name was,

1170
01:36:14,276 --> 01:36:17,487
- he's delusional?
- Oh extremely. He can be quite upsetting.

1171
01:36:17,487 --> 01:36:20,657
In fact, two weeks ago, a patient
got so wound up

1172
01:36:20,657 --> 01:36:24,744
by one of Noyce's stories
that he beat him up.

1173
01:36:24,911 --> 01:36:26,538
Cigarette?

1174
01:36:27,914 --> 01:36:29,791
Oh. No, thanks.
I quit.

1175
01:36:31,376 --> 01:36:33,545
So, you're taking the ferry?

1176
01:36:34,087 --> 01:36:35,505
Oh yes. Absolutely. I uh...

1177
01:36:36,172 --> 01:36:38,049
I think we've gotten
all we came here for so.

1178
01:36:38,883 --> 01:36:40,093
"We" marshal?

1179
01:36:42,304 --> 01:36:44,097
Speaking of which. Have you

1180
01:36:44,514 --> 01:36:47,017
- seen him, Doctor?
- Who?

1181
01:36:47,851 --> 01:36:49,519
My partner, Chuck.

1182
01:36:52,230 --> 01:36:54,316
You don't have a partner, Marshal.
You came here alone.

1183
01:36:56,818 --> 01:36:59,446
You know, I've built something valuable here.

1184
01:36:59,446 --> 01:37:03,074
And valuable things have a way of
being misunderstood in their own time.

1185
01:37:03,074 --> 01:37:05,118
Everyone wants a quick fix,
they always have.

1186
01:37:05,160 --> 01:37:08,830
I'm trying to do something that people,
yourself included, don't understand.

1187
01:37:08,830 --> 01:37:11,416
And I'm not going to give up
without a fight.

1188
01:37:12,751 --> 01:37:15,420
I can see that...

1189
01:37:19,132 --> 01:37:21,092
So tell me again
about your partner.

1190
01:37:22,969 --> 01:37:24,971
What partner?

1191
01:38:29,953 --> 01:38:31,705
Marshal...

1192
01:38:32,998 --> 01:38:34,499
Going somewhere?

1193
01:38:34,958 --> 01:38:38,753
No. Just heading out
to the ferry. So...

1194
01:38:40,297 --> 01:38:42,007
I'm afraid it's the other way.

1195
01:38:45,010 --> 01:38:46,970
If you wait a moment,

1196
01:38:47,470 --> 01:38:50,557
I'll find someone who can take you
to the dock.

1197
01:38:54,269 --> 01:38:56,855
What is this, doctor?

1198
01:38:56,855 --> 01:38:59,482
It's just a sedative.

1199
01:38:59,482 --> 01:39:02,194
- It's for precaution.
- Precaution?

1200
01:39:04,613 --> 01:39:09,034
What are you going to do?
Kill me? Marshal.

1201
01:39:09,409 --> 01:39:10,785
You think you deserve it?

1202
01:39:11,244 --> 01:39:14,206
For what?
For provoking you?

1203
01:39:14,623 --> 01:39:17,292
and, forgive me,
what doesn't provoke you?

1204
01:39:17,626 --> 01:39:18,835
Remarks...

1205
01:39:19,211 --> 01:39:20,670
- Words...
- Nazis!

1206
01:39:21,505 --> 01:39:23,131
Well that, too.

1207
01:39:23,590 --> 01:39:25,425
And of course, memories, dreams...

1208
01:39:26,593 --> 01:39:30,847
Did you know that the word "trauma" comes
from the Greek for "wound"?

1209
01:39:31,181 --> 01:39:35,477
And what is the German word for "dream"
"Traumen".

1210
01:39:35,477 --> 01:39:36,645
Traumen.

1211
01:39:37,979 --> 01:39:40,899
Wounds can create monsters.

1212
01:39:41,107 --> 01:39:43,819
And you ...
you are wounded, marshal.

1213
01:39:44,736 --> 01:39:47,781
Wouldn't you agree,
when you see a monster

1214
01:39:48,490 --> 01:39:50,033
you must stop it?

1215
01:39:53,078 --> 01:39:55,247
- I agree.
- Yes...

1216
01:40:41,793 --> 01:40:43,628
What are you doing, baby?

1217
01:40:48,884 --> 01:40:50,594
You've got to get to the ferry.

1218
01:40:51,178 --> 01:40:53,472
No. No.
No.

1219
01:40:57,559 --> 01:41:01,646
If the world thinks that Chuck is dead,
then he is perfect for their experiments.

1220
01:41:02,147 --> 01:41:04,816
There's only one place they'd take him.

1221
01:41:07,360 --> 01:41:09,946
You go there and you'll die.

1222
01:41:09,946 --> 01:41:14,117
He's my partner. If they are hurting him, if they are
holding him against his will, I've got to bring him out.

1223
01:41:14,326 --> 01:41:16,495
I can't lose anyone else.

1224
01:41:17,079 --> 01:41:21,416
Don't go, Teddy.
Please don't do this. Don't go.

1225
01:41:24,252 --> 01:41:26,296
I'm sorry, honey.

1226
01:41:28,006 --> 01:41:30,801
I love this thing because
you gave it to me

1227
01:41:33,512 --> 01:41:35,597
But the truth is ...

1228
01:41:35,597 --> 01:41:38,767
it's one fucking ugly tie.

1229
01:42:19,099 --> 01:42:20,308
No!

1230
01:43:42,099 --> 01:43:44,059
Don't move!
Stay where you are!

1231
01:43:45,644 --> 01:43:47,396
Are you going to kill me?

1232
01:43:47,729 --> 01:43:52,025
No.
I'm not gonna kill you.

1233
01:45:44,054 --> 01:45:47,057
Why are you all wet, baby?

1234
01:45:48,100 --> 01:45:50,727
- What did you say?
- You know exactly what I said.

1235
01:46:04,074 --> 01:46:06,660
The rifle's empty by the way.

1236
01:46:12,207 --> 01:46:14,167
Have a seat.

1237
01:46:20,841 --> 01:46:24,219
For god's sake dry off
you're going to catch a cold.

1238
01:46:25,220 --> 01:46:26,305
Alright.

1239
01:46:28,974 --> 01:46:31,893
How badly did you hurt the guard?

1240
01:46:34,479 --> 01:46:36,815
I don't know what
you're talking about.

1241
01:46:39,526 --> 01:46:41,236
Yes. He's here.

1242
01:46:41,695 --> 01:46:44,907
Have Dr.Sheehan take a good look
at your man before you send him up.

1243
01:46:46,491 --> 01:46:48,452
So, Dr. Shehan...

1244
01:46:48,994 --> 01:46:50,329
He came on the ferry
this morning, huh?

1245
01:46:51,330 --> 01:46:52,414
Not exactly.

1246
01:46:54,166 --> 01:46:56,835
You blew up my car.
I really loved that car.

1247
01:46:58,128 --> 01:46:59,922
Sorry to hear about that.

1248
01:47:03,342 --> 01:47:05,010
Tremors are getting pretty bad.

1249
01:47:06,345 --> 01:47:07,512
How are the hallucinations?

1250
01:47:08,513 --> 01:47:10,057
Get out of here, Teddy.

1251
01:47:11,225 --> 01:47:13,185
This place is gonna be the end of you.

1252
01:47:16,188 --> 01:47:19,066
- Not bad.
- They'll get worse.

