02:07:19,100 --> 02:07:23,604
And I murdered my wife
in the spring of '52.

1500
02:07:48,170 --> 02:07:50,172
How we doing this morning?

1501
02:07:50,590 --> 02:07:52,258
Good.
And You?

1502
02:07:52,341 --> 02:07:54,552
Can't complain.

1503
02:08:03,311 --> 02:08:05,062
So what's our next move?

1504
02:08:05,771 --> 02:08:07,231
You tell me.

1505
02:08:12,862 --> 02:08:14,614
I've gotta get off this rock,
Chuck.

1506
02:08:17,033 --> 02:08:20,620
Get back to the mainland. Whatever the
hell is going on here. It's bad.

1507
02:08:41,933 --> 02:08:44,227
Don't worry, partner.
They're not gonna catch us.

1508
02:08:51,192 --> 02:08:52,902
That's right. We're too smart for them.

1509
02:08:54,946 --> 02:08:56,197
Yeah, we are.
Aren't we?

1510
02:09:12,922 --> 02:09:15,299
You know this place makes
me wonder.

1511
02:09:16,217 --> 02:09:17,677
Yeah? What's that boss?

1512
02:09:19,178 --> 02:09:20,304
Which would be worse?

1513
02:09:21,889 --> 02:09:23,933
To live as a monster ...

1514
02:09:24,559 --> 02:09:27,019
or to die as a good man.

1515
02:09:35,820 --> 02:09:37,905
Teddy?

